    Definitions:
    - "Semiconductor-based" = built on semiconductor substrate, made of semiconductor materials, or manufactured by semiconductor technology where semiconductor plays critical role;
    - "Physical or chemical phenomena" = pressure, acoustic waves, acceleration, vibration, movement, orientation, strain, magnetic field strength, electric field strength, light, radioactivity, humidity, flow, chemical concentration;
    - "Semiconductor-based sensor" = detects physical or chemical quantities and converts to electric signals;
    - "Semiconductor-based actuator" = converts electric signals into physical movement;
    - "Semiconductor-based resonator" = generates mechanical or electrical oscillation of predefined frequency in response to external input;
    - "Semiconductor-based oscillator" = generates mechanical or electrical oscillation of predefined frequency.

